&lt;p&gt;Jenni Kayne is a California-based lifestyle brand that aims to empower an elevated approach to everyday living. Whether it’s our edited style ethos or coveted interiors sensibility, we work hard to create a world that&#39;s inviting and intentional. From our stores across the country to our operations and corporate teams, we believe in the power of a workplace that’s built on diversity and inclusion—where the varied voices and viewpoints of our community pave the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Picking Lead at Jenni Kayne, you will oversee daily picking and replenishment operations within the distribution center. This role is responsible for driving productivity, accuracy, and team engagement while ensuring inventory integrity and operational excellence across all picking functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;586&quot; data-end=&quot;618&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;586&quot; data-end=&quot;618&quot;&gt;Team Leadership &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;619&quot; data-end=&quot;1248&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;619&quot; data-end=&quot;779&quot; data-section-id=&quot;7fpr8s&quot;&gt;Lead and support associates responsible for replenishing pick modules, ensuring inventory is accurately stocked in correct bin locations without overfilling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;780&quot; data-end=&quot;897&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1q3y5sc&quot;&gt;Oversee all picking activities, including use of the 6RS Chuck system and RF Smart scanning for order fulfillment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;898&quot; data-end=&quot;1014&quot; data-section-id=&quot;i92k1a&quot;&gt;Supervise resolution of “hospital” orders (incomplete/missing items) to ensure accurate and timely order closure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1015&quot; data-end=&quot;1132&quot; data-section-id=&quot;3cwfn7&quot;&gt;Communicate clear direction to team members while fostering a positive, engaged, and accountable team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1133&quot; data-end=&quot;1248&quot; data-section-id=&quot;14pg0oy&quot;&gt;Set performance expectations and ensure achievement of key metrics related to productivity, quality, and safety&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1250&quot; data-end=&quot;1284&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;1250&quot; data-end=&quot;1284&quot;&gt;Inventory &amp;amp; Systems Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1285&quot; data-end=&quot;1674&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1285&quot; data-end=&quot;1434&quot; data-section-id=&quot;og1sjy&quot;&gt;Maintain a strong understanding of warehouse management systems and troubleshoot issues by partnering with appropriate internal or external teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1435&quot; data-end=&quot;1524&quot; data-section-id=&quot;cjavks&quot;&gt;Ensure all inventory transactions, counts, and system updates are executed accurately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1525&quot; data-end=&quot;1592&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1tihdqv&quot;&gt;Support cycle counts and physical inventory processes as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1593&quot; data-end=&quot;1674&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1u64oc3&quot;&gt;Monitor product quality and escalate issues to prevent operational disruption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1676&quot; data-end=&quot;1712&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;1676&quot; data-end=&quot;1712&quot;&gt;Warehouse Standards &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1713&quot; data-end=&quot;2052&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1713&quot; data-end=&quot;1815&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1gz2t78&quot;&gt;Maintain the organization, cleanliness, and overall condition of the pick module and bin locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1816&quot; data-end=&quot;1894&quot; data-section-id=&quot;1rlqc7z&qu

&lt;p&gt;Jenni Kayne is a California-based lifestyle brand that aims to empower an elevated approach to everyday living. Whether it’s our edited style ethos or coveted interiors sensibility, we work hard to create a world that&#39;s inviting and intentional. From our stores across the country to our operations and corporate teams, we believe in the power of a workplace that’s built on diversity and inclusion—where the varied voices and viewpoints of our community pave the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic Product Development &amp;amp; Production Associate to supports the day-to-day operations of the Product Development and Production team by coordinating samples, materials, and vendor communication to ensure all seasonal milestones are met. This role will work closely with cross-functional partners and external vendors to execute the development from concept through production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role and Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Product Development &amp;amp; Production Associate, your primary responsibilities include the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Product Development and Production team in tracking WIPs, fabrics, samples and approvals to ensure calendar milestones are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and organize vendor packages, including swatches, reference samples, and shipment documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and track sample and material shipments, keeping the team updated on timing and delivery status.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate data in PLM, WIP trackers, costing sheets, and production calendars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the execution of the seasonal SKU plan for Apparel, Shoes, and Accessories, helping ensure all deadlines are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up with vendors and internal teams to support on-time development and production milestones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with item and purchase order creation and updates in ERP system (Netsuite).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional administrative and operational tasks as needed to support the Product Development and Production team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative thinker with a strong eye for detail and appreciation for quality craftsmanship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–3 years of experience in product development, production, or a related role within apparel, footwear, or accessories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized, with the ability to manage multiple moving parts while keeping timelines and priorities in check.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong in Excel and comfortable navigating Microsoft Office and digital tracking tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with PLM (WFX a plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with ERP (Netsuite a plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player who thrives in a collaborative, fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear and confident communicator — written, verbal, and visual.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curious, proactive, and eager to learn from others while taking initiative where you can.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to sit, stand, bend, stoop, lift up to 30 lbs, and move between work areas throughout the day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Notes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This job description is not all inclusive. In addition, Kayne LLC dba Jenni Kayne reserves the right to amend this job description at any time. Kayne LLC is an Equal Opportunity Employer, committed to a diverse and inclusive work environment. &amp;nbsp;The annual base salary range for this position is $80,000 - 85,000. The base salary is determined by experience, education, skills, and location.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

